CatDescriptText: Miss Cathy Shrinar, nurse, Broadhead Road, Aliquippa, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 10, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "How do you think Soviet Premier Khrushchev's visit to the United States affected relations between our country and Russia? Were you or were you not impressed by his visit to Pittsburgh?" answer reads: "That's something you cannot tell right away."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Cathy Shrinar, wearing light colored short sleeved blouse, holding magazine and sweater over arm, standing on Liberty Avenue, in front of Jenkins Arcade, May Building with Thrift Drugs in background
